 <!-- Introduction -->
 <!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
 <purpose>
   <p>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module to record an involvement in an individual activity.</p>
<p>The nature of an involvement in an individual activity may be specified by
indicating a class of involvement in which it is a member.</p>
<example><p>The involvment of John Doe, who is a stress engineer
at Joe Bloggs and Co. in the stress analysis of part XYZ_123 carried out on
2001-05-02 is an <b>individual_involvement_in_activity</b>.</p>
<p>This individual involvement is classified as a member of the
<b>class_of_involvement_in_activity</b> 'stress analysis performer'.</p>
</example>
 </purpose>

 <!-- Items in scope -->
 <inscope>
<li><p>a individual product, document, person, organization or other activity that is involved in an individual activity.</p></li> </inscope>

 <!-- Items out of scope -->
 <outscope>
<li><p> class of involvement in activity;</p>
<note number="1">Class of involvement in activity is within the scope of
the <module_ref linkend="class_of_involvement_in_activity:1_scope">Class_of_involvement_in_activity</module_ref> application module.</note>
</li>
<li><p>membership of a class of involvement in activity.</p>
<note number="2">Membership of a class of involvement in activity is
within the scope of the <module_ref linkend="activity_structure_and_classification:1_scope">Activity_structure_and_classification</module_ref> application module.</note>
</li>
 </outscope>

